1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,640
Hello everyone and welcome back to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,640
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:11,800
My name is Catherine and today we've got a very nerve-wracking situation for you.
我是Catherine，今天我们给大家带来一个非常紧张的场景。

4
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:12,800
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,560
We are going to meet the in-laws.
我们要去见未来的岳父母/公婆。

6
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:16,560
Meeting the in-laws.
见未来的岳父母/公婆。

7
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:17,800
So who are in-laws?
那么，什么是“in-laws”？

8
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:21,960
These are the parents of your husband or wife.
就是你丈夫或妻子的父母。

9
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:22,960
Right.
对。

10
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:26,720
So in this case, you have the mother-in-law and your father-in-law.
所以在这种情况下，有岳母/婆婆和岳父/公公。

11
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:27,720
That's right.
没错。

12
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:30,120
We're meeting these people for the very first time.
我们是第一次见这些人。

13
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:35,200
You can imagine how nervous the man is who's meeting his future wife's parents.
你可以想象这个男人有多紧张，他要见未来妻子的父母。

14
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:40,440
Let's learn all about what they talk about in today's dialogue.
让我们来了解今天对话中他们谈论的内容。

15
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:50,440
Mother, father, I'd like to introduce you to my fiancé, Bob.
妈妈，爸爸，我想给你们介绍一下我的未婚夫，Bob。

16
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:51,760
Hello, Bob.
你好，Bob。

17
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:52,760
Welcome.
欢迎。

18
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:53,760
Thanks for having me.
谢谢你们邀请我。

19
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:54,760
Nice to meet the both of you.
很高兴见到你们两位。

20
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,520
I've heard so much.
我听说过很多。

21
00:00:56,520 --> 00:01:01,040
So Cindy told you about bringing home her last boyfriend then.
所以Cindy告诉过你她带回家上一个男朋友的事吧。

22
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:02,040
That idiot.
那个白痴。

23
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:03,040
Shhh, Thurston.
嘘，Thurston。

24
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,040
You're going to scare the poor boy.
你会吓到那个可怜的小伙子的。

25
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,920
Come in and have a drink.
进来喝一杯吧。

26
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,240
Dinner will be on in just a bit.
晚餐马上就好。

27
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:09,240
What will you be having?
你想喝什么？

28
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:10,280
Whiskey, bourbon?
威士忌，波本？

29
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,120
Pick your poison.
选你的毒药吧。

30
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:14,120
If you have a lemonade, that'd be great.
如果有柠檬水的话，那就太好了。

31
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,120
Lemonade?
柠檬水？

32
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,120
Why, sure.
哦，当然有。

33
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,120
There's some in the fridge.
冰箱里有一些。

34
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,160
Mother makes her own lemonade from scratch.
妈妈自己从头开始做柠檬水。

35
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:20,320
It's the best.
最好喝了。

36
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:22,080
So what are your hobbies, son?
那么，你有什么爱好，孩子？

37
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:24,400
If you want, we can do some hunting tomorrow.
如果你愿意，我们明天可以去打猎。

38
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,680
I've just picked up a new rifle I've been meaning to try out.
我刚买了一把新步枪，一直想试试。

39
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:27,680
It should be a real hoot.
应该会很有趣。

40
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:32,120
Um, I'm not really, uh, I don't really hunt.
嗯，我不太，呃，我不太打猎。

41
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,120
You don't hunt?
你不打猎？

42
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,840
Well, I'll beat damn.
好吧，真见鬼。

43
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:37,040
Bob is an animal rights activist.
Bob是个动物权利活动家。

44
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:38,680
He doesn't believe in harming animals.
他不相信伤害动物。

45
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,680
Dinner's ready.
晚餐准备好了。

46
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:43,400
Let's go out to the patio where the pig is roasting.
我们去院子里吧，那里正在烤猪。

47
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,400
Roast pig?
烤猪？

48
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:47,400
I'm a vegetarian.
我是素食主义者。

49
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:51,680
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

50
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:54,160
So a very awkward situation.
真是个尴尬的局面。

51
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:58,360
I think they might have a little bit of a problems in the future.
我想他们未来可能会有点问题。

52
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:03,800
Yeah, there's there are a lot of cultural differences between the characters, the son-in-law
是的，角色之间有很多文化差异，这个女婿

53
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,800
and the new parents, the father.
和新父母，父亲之间。

54
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,480
So it's really interesting.
所以真的很有趣。

55
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:16,800
Why don't we start off by looking at a couple of different words on language takeaway.
我们不如先看看“语言要点”中的几个单词。

56
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,840
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

57
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:23,380
So first of all, we have the two characters, Cindy and Bob, who are getting married.
首先，我们有Cindy和Bob这两个角色，他们要结婚了。

58
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:26,800
So we call them, we call Bob, Cindy's fiance.
所以我们称Bob为Cindy的未婚夫。

59
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,800
Right.
对。

60
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,560
So my fiance.
所以我的未婚夫。

61
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:33,360
And it's, uh, it comes from French and it means to the person that you're going to get
它来自法语，意思是你将要

62
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,360
married to.
结婚的人。

63
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,360
That's right.
没错。

64
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,840
The person you've decided to get married to.
你决定要结婚的人。

65
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,800
So we say fiance.
所以我们说fiancé。

66
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,320
We can say the same word for a man or a woman.
这个词对男人或女人都可以用。

67
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:43,000
So he is my fiance.
所以他是我的未婚夫。

68
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,360
She is my fiance.
她是我的未婚妻。

69
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,360
Okay.
好的。

70
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,360
My fiance.
我的未婚夫/未婚妻。

71
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,360
Very good.
很好。

72
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:52,240
So Cindy introduces her fiance, Bob, to her parents and they start talking a little bit
所以Cindy把她的未婚夫Bob介绍给她的父母，他们开始聊了一会儿，

73
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:58,800
and her dad, Thurston, invites him to go do some hunting tomorrow.
她的父亲Thurston邀请他明天去打猎。

74
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,800
That's right.
没错。

75
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:05,840
So hunting is a sport in America and lots of places in the world where you shoot animals.
所以打猎是美国和世界上很多地方的一项运动，就是射杀动物。

76
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:06,840
Okay.
好的。

77
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:11,960
So you go in the woods, you wear brown and green colors and you shoot animals to take
所以你去树林里，穿着棕色和绿色的衣服，射杀动物，然后

78
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:16,240
them home and skin them and eat them or to keep them as trophies.
带回家剥皮吃掉，或者作为战利品保存。

79
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,240
All right.
好的。

80
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:22,640
So you go hunting and well, the way that you shoot these animals is you need to have a
所以你去打猎，而射杀这些动物的方式是你需要有一把

81
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:23,640
rifle.
步枪。

82
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:24,640
A rifle.
一支步枪。

83
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:27,400
So you could also call it a hunting rifle in this case.
所以在这种情况下，你也可以称之为猎枪。

84
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:30,720
A rifle is a gun, but it's a very long gun.
步枪是一种枪，但它是一种很长的枪。

85
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,720
Right.
对。

86
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:34,240
So it's not a little gun that you just hold in your hand.
所以它不是那种你握在手里的小枪。

87
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,240
It's very long.
它很长。

88
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,360
It'll be maybe like half a meter, a meter long.
大概有半米到一米长。

89
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,360
That's right.
没错。

90
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:42,120
And so oftentimes people, when they're hunting, they lie on the ground and they wait for the
所以很多时候，人们打猎时，会趴在地上等待

91
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:46,600
animals to pass and they hide themselves and then they shoot from a long distance.
动物经过，他们隐藏自己，然后从远处射击。

92
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,600
Right.
对。

93
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,920
So he's talking about hunting.
所以他在谈论打猎。

94
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:52,560
He's got a new rifle and he says, yeah, we should definitely go.
他有一把新步枪，他说，是啊，我们真该去。

95
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,600
It should be a real hoot.
肯定会很有趣。

96
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,600
Should be a real hoot.
肯定会很有趣。

97
00:03:55,600 --> 00:04:00,280
This is a very fun spoken English phrase.
这是一个很有趣的口语短语。

98
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,760
It's said more by older people than by younger people.
年纪大的人比年轻人更常说。

99
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,840
So this is why the father says it in the dialogue.
所以这就是为什么对话中父亲会这么说。

100
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:09,480
A hoot should be a real good time, real fun.
“A hoot” 意思是玩得很开心，非常有趣。

101
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:13,080
So how can you can use this like, oh, the party last night was a real hoot.
所以你可以这样用，比如，昨晚的派对真有趣。

102
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,080
Yeah.
嗯。

103
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,080
You can say that.
你可以这么说。

104
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,520
You can say or she's a real hoot.
你也可以说，她真有趣。

105
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:17,520
She's really funny.
她真的很好笑。

106
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:18,520
Okay.
好的。

107
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:19,520
But it's really enjoyable.
但确实很愉快。

108
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:24,000
This is a little bit more like spoken and for used by maybe older people.
这更偏向口语，可能年纪大的人用得多。

109
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,720
My mother would say that I wouldn't say this.
我妈妈会这么说，但我不会。

110
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:28,520
So, oh my goodness, it was a real hoot.
所以，哦，天哪，那真有趣。

111
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:29,520
Yeah.
嗯。

112
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,520
All right.
好的。

113
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:33,800
So he's talking about hunting, how much fun they would have.
所以他在谈论打猎，以及他们会玩得多开心。

114
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:40,160
And unfortunately, Bob is an animal rights activist.
不幸的是，鲍勃是个动物权益活动家。

115
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:41,160
What does this mean?
这是什么意思？

116
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:45,440
So an animal rights activist is someone who is very concerned with protecting the rights
动物权益活动家是指非常关心保护动物权利

117
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,800
of animals.
的人。

118
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:52,960
So for example, if I'm an animal rights activist, maybe I will protest people who wear fur or
比如，如果我是动物权益活动家，我可能会抗议穿皮草的人，或者

119
00:04:52,960 --> 00:05:00,720
perhaps I will also try and secure land for a natural wildlife preserve so that animals
我还会努力争取土地建立自然野生动物保护区，让动物

120
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,720
can live in the wild.
能在野外生活。

121
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,800
There's not houses or cars.
没有房子或汽车。

122
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:08,800
So animal rights activists are people who try to make sure that animals are protected
所以动物权益活动家是努力确保动物

123
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,080
from human beings.
免受人类伤害的人。

124
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,320
Okay, very good.
好的，很好。

125
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,420
And this is what Bob is.
而鲍勃就是这样的人。

126
00:05:13,420 --> 00:05:15,880
So obviously Bob is not really into hunting, right?
所以显然鲍勃不太喜欢打猎，对吧？

127
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,880
I'm guessing no.
我猜是不喜欢。

128
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,800
These are two opposites.
这是两个对立面。

129
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:24,040
You have people who like to kill animals and people who want to protect the lives of animals.
有喜欢杀动物的人，也有想保护动物生命的人。

130
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,040
Right.
对。

131
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,040
Okay.
好的。

132
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:29,920
Well, and to finish off our language takeaway, dinner is ready.
好了，为了结束我们的语言要点环节，晚餐准备好了。

133
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,440
So let's go out to the patio.
所以我们去露台吧。

134
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,440
Okay.
好的。

135
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:39,120
A patio is a space outside the house, usually in the back that's paved.
露台是房子外面的空间，通常在后面，铺有地面。

136
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:42,560
So there's like cement or bricks or some kind of tile.
比如有水泥、砖块或某种瓷砖。

137
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:46,640
And that's where you have a table and chairs or some place to sit and rest.
那里有桌子和椅子，或者可以坐和休息的地方。

138
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,120
This is where you have a grill.
那里有烤架。

139
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,360
So it's an outdoor area, but it's not grass.
所以它是一个户外区域，但不是草地。

140
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,360
Okay.
好的。

141
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,360
So it's not your backyard.
所以它不是你的后院。

142
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,260
Oh, it could be in your backyard.
哦，它可以在你的后院。

143
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:57,040
The patio could be in the backyard.
露台可以在后院。

144
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,040
That's right.
没错。

145
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,400
But the ground in the patio is not grass.
但露台的地面不是草地。

146
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:03,040
It's some kind of material like cement or brick or wood.
是某种材料，比如水泥、砖块或木头。

147
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,080
Okay, very good.
好的，很好。

148
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:05,240
So great words there.
这些词很棒。

149
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:11,440
Why don't we listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit with Fluency Builder.
我们为什么不听一遍对话，然后稍后回来进行流利度训练。

150
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,600
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

151
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,360
So we have three great phrases here on Fluency Builder.
所以我们在流利度训练中有三个很棒的短语。

152
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:19,240
Why don't we start off with the first one?
我们先从第一个开始吧？

153
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:22,600
So the first one, we have to go back to the very beginning of this dialogue and think
第一个，我们要回到这个对话的最开始，想想

154
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:27,080
about these people who are introducing each other for the very first time.
这些第一次互相介绍的人。

155
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:30,400
Cindy says, I want to introduce you to my fiance, Bob.
辛迪说，我想把你介绍给我的未婚夫鲍勃。

156
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:34,480
Bob says to Cindy's parents, I've heard so much.
鲍勃对辛迪的父母说，久仰大名。

157
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,240
I've heard so much.
久仰大名。

158
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,240
Okay.
好的。

159
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:42,960
So this phrase, you can usually use it when you meet somebody for the first time.
所以这个短语，你通常可以在第一次见到某人时使用。

160
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,960
I've heard so much about you.
久仰大名。

161
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:45,960
That's right.
没错。

162
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,960
So the longer version is I've heard so much about you.
所以更长的版本是“久仰大名”。

163
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:52,280
Basically you're saying, listen, Cindy talks about you a lot.
基本上你在说，听着，辛迪经常提起你。

164
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,880
I've heard really nice things.
我听到了很多好话。

165
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,880
Sometimes people like to joke.
有时候人们喜欢开玩笑。

166
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,640
You say, I've heard so much about you.
你说，“久仰大名。”

167
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,560
They say, I hope only good things.
他们会说，“希望都是好话。”

168
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,880
Yeah, I hope not too much.
是啊，希望没说得太多。

169
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,400
I hope not too much.
希望没说得太多。

170
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:07,720
So this is a very polite way to respond when someone introduces themselves.
所以这是别人自我介绍时一种非常礼貌的回应方式。

171
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,720
Okay.
好的。

172
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,880
